The Nigerian Communications commission yesterday decried the increasing rate of cybercrimes in the country. The NCC called on service providers to collaborate with it in educating their consumers on how to safeguard themselves against cybercriminals. The Director, Consumer Affairs Bureau of the NCC, Felicia Onwoegbuchulam, made the call in Kano yesterday during the commission’s 52nd edition of consumer town hall meeting. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY Represented by the Deputy Director, Consumer Affairs Bureau, Alhaji Isma’il Adedigba, Onwoegbuchalam said the meeting was aimed at sensitizing the consumers on the dangers associated to cybercrimes. She said without educating the consumers about cybercrime trends and ensuring safe use of connected devices, cybercriminals would continue to make cyberspace unsafe. She described consumers as key stakeholders in the ongoing fight against cybercrimes in the country. NCC to unveil internet industry code this year NCC takes enlightenment campaign against cybercrime to Niger NCC takes cybercrime campaign to Ibadan Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin